<div style="columns:3;column-gap:24px;font-size:12px;line-height:1.5;">

<p><strong>System Metrics</strong><br>
CPU usage, RAM utilization, and system load averages. Disable only on extremely resource-constrained servers where minimizing polling overhead is critical.</p>

<p><strong>Array Status</strong><br>
Parity validity, disk assignments, and overall array health. Leave enabled unless you run Unraid strictly as a Docker/VM host without a storage array.</p>

<p><strong>Disk Health</strong><br>
SMART attributes, drive temperatures, and spin-down states. Disable if drives are behind a hardware RAID controller that blocks SMART pass-through.</p>

<p><strong>Network</strong><br>
Interface packet statistics, bandwidth throughput, and link states. Safe to leave enabled on all setups.</p>

<p><strong>Docker</strong><br>
Container up/down status, CPU, memory, and network usage per container. Disable if the Docker service is turned off on your server.</p>

<p><strong>Virtual Machines</strong><br>
VM power states, vCPU usage, and allocated RAM via libvirt. Disable if you do not use Unraid's KVM virtualization.</p>

<p><strong>GPU Metrics</strong><br>
Utilization, VRAM usage, and temperatures for NVIDIA, AMD, or Intel GPUs. Disable if your server has no GPUs installed or passed through.</p>

<p><strong>UPS Status</strong><br>
Battery capacity, load, and estimated runtime from Unraid's built-in APC/CyberPower daemon. Disable if no UPS is connected via USB.</p>

<p><strong>NUT Plugin</strong><br>
Network UPS Tools integration for advanced or networked UPS monitoring. Disable if the NUT plugin is not installed.</p>

<p><strong>Hardware Info</strong><br>
Static details: motherboard model, CPU type, PCI devices. Polls infrequently since this data rarely changes. Safe to leave enabled.</p>

<p><strong>User Shares</strong><br>
Free space, allocation, and configuration per Unraid share. Disable if calculating share sizes causes high I/O on very large arrays.</p>

<p><strong>ZFS Pools</strong><br>
Vdev health, scrub status, and ARC memory usage. Disable if you do not use ZFS on your server.</p>

<p><strong>Unassigned Devices</strong><br>
Drives mounted outside the array via the Unassigned Devices plugin. Disable if this plugin is not installed.</p>

<p><strong>Notifications</strong> <em>(internal)</em><br>
Captures Unraid system notifications and alerts. Interval-only &mdash; cannot be disabled.</p>

<p><strong>License Info</strong> <em>(internal)</em><br>
Checks OS version, registration tier, and device limits. Interval-only &mdash; cannot be disabled.</p>

<p><strong>Fan Control</strong> <em>(internal)</em><br>
Fan RPMs and PWM states, integrates with Dynamix Auto Fan. Disable if fans are controlled by BIOS or an external controller.</p>

<p><strong>Tuning</strong> <em>(internal)</em><br>
CPU frequency scaling and disk tunable parameters. Disable if you run standard Unraid defaults without Tips &amp; Tweaks.</p>

</div>
</blockquote>

