<blockquote class="inline_help">
<div style="columns:3;column-gap:24px;font-size:12px;line-height:1.5;">

<p><strong>API Port</strong><br>
TCP port the REST API listens on (default 8043). Change if another service conflicts.</p>

<p><strong>CORS Origin</strong><br>
<code>Access-Control-Allow-Origin</code> header. Use <code>*</code> for all origins or restrict to a domain like <code>https://homeassistant.local</code>.</p>

<p><strong>Read-Only Mode</strong><br>
Disables all write/control endpoints (Docker start/stop, array commands). Use for monitoring-only setups.</p>

<p><strong>Log Level</strong><br>
Verbosity of <code>/var/log/unraid-agent-dev.log</code>. Use <em>debug</em> when troubleshooting, <em>info</em> for normal operation.</p>

<p><strong>MCP stdio</strong><br>
An alternative launch mode for local MCP access. The binary acts as a local MCP server over stdin/stdout without starting an HTTP server. Only needed when running an MCP client directly on the Unraid box.</p>

<p><strong>MQTT — Local (embedded)</strong><br>
The agent runs a built-in MQTT broker (mochi-mqtt) on this Unraid box. No external broker required — ideal for getting started or Home Assistant setups. Migrate to a remote broker at any time by switching the mode.</p>

<p><strong>MQTT — Remote</strong><br>
Publishes system metrics to an existing MQTT broker (e.g., Mosquitto). Enter the broker host and port. Credentials are optional if the broker allows anonymous connections.</p>

<p><strong>Embedded Broker — Bind to LAN</strong><br>
By default the embedded broker only accepts connections from localhost (127.0.0.1). Enabling Bind to LAN exposes port 1883 to your network. Always set a password when Bind to LAN is on.</p>

<p><strong>QoS Level</strong><br>
0 = fire-and-forget, 1 = acknowledged delivery, 2 = exactly-once. Use 0 for metrics; 1 or 2 for critical alerts.</p>

<p><strong>Retain Messages</strong><br>
Retained messages are stored by the broker and delivered immediately to new subscribers, ensuring they get the latest state.</p>

<p><strong>HA Discovery</strong><br>
Publishes MQTT auto-discovery messages so entities appear automatically in Home Assistant without manual configuration.</p>

<p><strong>TLS</strong><br>
Encrypts the MQTT connection to a remote broker. Default port for TLS is 8883. Skip Verify only with self-signed certificates. TLS is not applicable to the embedded broker.</p>

</div>
</blockquote>

